history.content: Can't say what 162 & 170 would look like, but taking 186 and 170 together this semester hasn't been too bad so far, although both classes require a decent time investment. With 170 there are the weekly homework sets that usually take me a little longer than 70, and 186 has 4 projects that are fairly straightforward but do take some time.

children.subject:
Definitely 170 + 186. 

I'm taking 162 + 186 together this semester, and it's manageable. I don't think I would manage 162 + 170 though.

history.content:
I'm a junior transfer, planning on studying abroad next spring. I'd like to complete 162 and 170 by next fall (2020) but I'm not sure how realistic it would be to take those in the same semester. I'm pretty set on taking 170 in Fall, and I was wondering if there was any difference in difficulty in taking 186 vs 162 alongside that.

I'm taking 61c + 70 this semester and I find the workload to be manageable but the content to be a little tough (70 moreso than 61c); I'm doing fairly well but I'm not doing a great job of keeping up with lecture / discussion in either class. I think that might be a work ethic / time management thing more than anything else. 

Any thoughts or advice regarding this would be really appreciated, thanks!
history.subject: CS 162 + 170 vs 186 + 170
